{"lemma":"دَنِيَّةٍ","slug":"دَنِيَّةٍ","root":"د.ن.#","root_slug":"د-ن-_","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ن-_","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13181","n13229","n13235"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"near, neighboring"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"low"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"mean"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"vile"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"worthless, of a bad quality"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"weak-minded, cowardly"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the roots د ن و (d n w) and د ن ي (d n y)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13181","headword_ar":"دِنِّيَّةٌ","root":"dn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of cap called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalanosuwap","text_ar":"قَلَنْسُوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", of a Kádee; likened to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dan~","text_ar":"دَنّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qlnswp","text_ar":"قلنسوة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worn by Kádees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though so called in relation to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dan~","text_ar":"دَنّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high and round:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 109:) accord. to Esh-Shereeshee, originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daniynapN","text_ar":"دَنِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qlnswp","text_ar":"قلنسوة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pointed at the extremity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in my original"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlATrAf","text_ar":"الاطراف"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~araf","text_ar":"الطَّرَف"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worn by Kádees and great men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"not a genuine Arabic word, but of the dial. of El-'Irák. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13229","headword_ar":"دِنْيَةٌ","root":"dnw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, in five places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13235","headword_ar":"دَنِيَّهٌ","root":"dnw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"base, quality, property, natural disposition, habit, practice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"action;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqiySapN","text_ar":"نَقِيصَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is blamed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daniyoy^apN","text_ar":"دَنِيْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danaAyaA","text_ar":"دَنَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Har p. 327.) Hence the saying of Ibn-Háritheh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almaniy~apa laA Ald~aniy~apa","text_ar":"المَنِيَّةَ لَا الدَّنِيَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning I choose"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"death rather than,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not, disgrace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har ubi suprà.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A/","headword_ar":"دني","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_51","lexicon_en":"Habib Anthony Salmone, An Advanced Learner's Arabic-English Dictionary (1889)","lexicon_ar":"حبيب سالمون، قاموس عربي انجليزي متقدم للمتعلمين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=135904#541cef","body_html":"دني<br> دَنِيَ(n. ac. دَنًا [ ]دَنَايَة [] )<br>a. Was vile, contemptible.<br> <br> دَنَّيَa. Drew near, made to come near.<br> b. [Fī], Busied himself about trifles. <br> دَاْنَيَa. Drew together, connected, contracted.<br> <br> أَدْنَيَa. Drew near, made to come near.<br> <br> تَدَنَّيَa. Drew near little by little.<br> <br> تَدَاْنَيَa. Were or drew near to one another, close <br> together.<br> <br> إِسْتَدْنَيَa. Asked to come nearer. <br> دَانٍ (pl.<br> دُنَاة [] )<br>a. Near; approaching.<br> <br> دَنَاوَة []<br>a. Proximity, nearness.<br> b. Relationship.<br> <br> دَنَايَة []<br>a. Baseness; pusillanimity.<br> <br> دَنِيّ [] (pl.<br> أَدْنِيَآء [] )<br>a. Vile, base, contemptible.<br> b. Near.<br> c. Relative; friend.<br> <br> دَنِيَّة [] (pl.<br> دَنَايَا)<br>a. Vile; base (thing). <br> دُنْيَا (pl.<br> دُنَي)<br>a. World, this present world.<br> <br> دُنْيَوِيّ دُنْيَاوِيّ<br> a. Worldly, of the world."}]}}